        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Doctor: structure shell completion repair",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis PR moves shell completion doctor repair onto the internal runnable health-check path while keeping the existing public health-check surface normalized.\n\nThe rule remains one flow: check shell completion status, return lint findings when repair is false, and run the existing repair actions when repair is true. `doctorShellCompletion()` stays as the positional presentation wrapper and now prints the structured warnings/changes returned by that flow.\n\nKey behavior:\n\n- `openclaw doctor --lint` can report slow dynamic completion profiles and missing completion cache as structured findings.\n- `openclaw doctor --fix` still repairs stale dynamic completion profiles and missing caches from the shell-completion position in doctor order.\n- Optional missing shell completion remains quiet in lint/non-interactive detection and still prompts only in repair mode.\n- Runnable checks are normalized at registry boundaries so public `openclaw/plugin-sdk/health` list/get consumers still receive detect-capable registered checks.\n\n## Verification\n\nBehavior addressed: shell completion doctor repair now participates in structured doctor lint/repair without exposing a public run-only SDK contract.\n\nReal environment tested: WSL Ubuntu 24.04 worktree rebased on latest `origin/main`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n- `git diff --check`\n- `node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/flows/health-check-registry.ts src/commands/doctor-completion.ts src/commands/doctor-completion.test.ts src/flows/doctor-core-checks.ts src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.ts src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.test.ts src/flows/doctor-lint-flow.ts src/flows/doctor-lint-flow.test.ts src/flows/doctor-repair-flow.ts`\n- `node_modules/.bin/oxlint src/flows/health-check-registry.ts src/commands/doctor-completion.ts src/commands/doctor-completion.test.ts src/flows/doctor-core-checks.ts src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.ts src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.test.ts src/flows/doctor-lint-flow.ts src/flows/doctor-lint-flow.test.ts src/flows/doctor-repair-flow.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/commands/doctor-completion.test.ts src/flows/doctor-lint-flow.test.ts src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.test.ts src/flows/doctor-repair-flow.test.ts src/flows/doctor-core-checks.test.ts src/flows/doctor-core-browser-residue-check.test.ts --reporter=dot`\n- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p tsconfig.core.json --noEmit --incremental false --pretty false`\n- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.core.test.json --noEmit --incremental false --pretty false`\n- `bash /tmp/codex-review --mode branch`\n\nEvidence after fix: focused Vitest passed 6 files / 56 tests; core tsgo and core test tsgo both passed; codex-review reported no actionable correctness issues.\n\nObserved result after fix: shell completion stale-cache and slow-dynamic cases are structured findings/repairs; optional install remains prompt-only in repair mode; public registry entries remain normalized.\n\nWhat was not tested: live mutation of a real user shell profile.\n",
